<p style="text-align: left;">
 
<span style="font-size: 25px;"><strong>c. 1956 &#8211; Breakfast Menu for the Covered Wagon Restaurant</strong></span>


<br>
Breakfast menu for the Covered Wagon Restaurant, found in a cupboard in Idlewild Lodge. Dated to the years that Jerry and Leslie Ann Dauth worked at the Covered Wagon.

<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Transcription</strong></i></span> 

<br>
<span style="font-size: 22px;"><i>The Covered Wagon Restaurant; Start The Day The Wrangler’s Way</i></span> 


<br>
<i>"Orange, Pineapple or Tomato Juice, Regular Size 15c, Extra Large 20c; ½ Grapefruit 20c; Sliced Oranges 20c; Breakfast Specials; (1) Sausage or Bacon or Ham, 2 Eggs, Buttered Toast, Jam and Coffee 90c; (2) Two Eggs (Real Hen Marbles) Buttered Toast and Coffee 50c; (3) One Egg, Toast and Coffee 35c; (4) Flapjacks, Old Fashioned Golden Brown, Served with Maple Syrup, Butter and Coffee 40c; With Side of Bacon, Ham or Sausage 75c; (5) French Toast (prepared with Homemade Bread), Maple Syrup, Butter and Coffee 50c; Dy Cereal with Milk 20c; Dry Cereal with Cream 30c; Drinks, Coffee 10c, Tea 10c, Milk 10c;"</i>





<br>

<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Details</strong></i></span> 


<br>
<i>Date: c. 1956</i>


<br>
<i>Location: USA, Colorado, Loveland, Idlewild</i>




<br>
<i>Source: Dauth Family Archive</i>


<br>


<i>Permalink:</i>
<a href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/c-1956-breakfast-menu-for-the-covered-wagon-restaurant/">https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/c-1956-breakfast-menu-for-the-covered-wagon-restaurant/</a>


<br><br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Related Posts</strong></i></span> 
<br>




<a href='https://www.idlewildlodge.org/posts/the-covered-wagon-restaurant/'>The Covered Wagon Restaurant</a>




</p>
<p>
