]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div data-parent="true" class="vc_row row-container" id="row-unique-2"><div class="row limit-width row-parent"><div class="wpb_row row-inner"><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-12 single-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode_text_column" ><div class="uncode-single-media  zoooom text-center animate_when_almost_visible alpha-anim"><div class="single-wrapper" style="max-width: 100%;"><div class="tmb tmb-light  tmb-shadowed tmb-shadowed-darker-std tmb-media-first tmb-media-last tmb-content-overlay tmb-no-bg"><div class="t-inside"><div class="t-entry-visual"><div class="t-entry-visual-tc"><div class="uncode-single-media-wrapper"><img class="wp-image-2975" src="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/wp-content/uploads/idlewild-archive-document-Document-c.-1950s-Idlewild-Lodge-Poem.jpg" width="1408" height="2000" alt=""></div>
					</div>
				</div></div></div></div></div>

</div></div></div></div></div></div><script id="script-row-unique-2" data-row="script-row-unique-2" type="text/javascript" class="vc_controls">UNCODE.initRow(document.getElementById("row-unique-2"));</script></div></div></div><div data-parent="true" class="vc_row row-container" id="row-unique-3"><div class="row limit-width row-parent"><div class="wpb_row row-inner"><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-12 single-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode_text_column text-lead" ></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">
 
<span style="font-size: 25px;"><strong>c. 1950s &#8211; Idlewild Lodge Poem</strong></span>


<br>
Poem on a piece of paper that closely resemble the words used in Idlewild Lodge advertisements in the 1950s. Most likely a brainstorm written by Anna Dauth who was managing Idlewild Lodge at the time. A sketch of Idlewild Lodge is at bottom, along with a horse.

<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Transcription</strong></i></span> 



<br>
<i>"Spend a vacation in comfort at Idlewild Lodge, Come in any kind of car a Plymouth or a Dodge. Modern electric lights, well furnished, good beds. If you don’t come your [you’re] losing your head. Riding horses available by week, month or season. You tell your friends that it is the best, that if you come to Idle Wild you’ll have comfort and rest."</i>


<br><br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>People</strong></i></span> 
<br>






Anna Dauth


<br>





<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Details</strong></i></span> 


<br>
<i>Date: c. 1950s</i>


<br>
<i>Location: USA, Colorado, Loveland, Idlewild</i>




<br>
<i>Source: Dauth Family Archive</i>


<br>


<i>Permalink:</i>
<a href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/c-1950s-idlewild-lodge-poem/">https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/c-1950s-idlewild-lodge-poem/</a>



</p>
<p>
</div></div></div></div></div></div><script id="script-row-unique-3" data-row="script-row-unique-3" type="text/javascript" class="vc_controls">UNCODE.initRow(document.getElementById("row-unique-3"));</script></div></div></div>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/c-1950s-idlewild-lodge-poem/">c. 1950s &#8211; Idlewild Lodge Poem</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org">Idlewild Lodge</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
