										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div data-parent="true" class="vc_row row-container" id="row-unique-6"><div class="row limit-width row-parent"><div class="wpb_row row-inner"><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-12 single-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode_text_column" ><div class="uncode-single-media  zoooom text-center animate_when_almost_visible alpha-anim"><div class="single-wrapper" style="max-width: 100%;"><div class="tmb tmb-light  tmb-shadowed tmb-shadowed-darker-std tmb-media-first tmb-media-last tmb-content-overlay tmb-no-bg"><div class="t-inside"><div class="t-entry-visual"><div class="t-entry-visual-tc"><div class="uncode-single-media-wrapper"><img class="wp-image-2969" src="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/wp-content/uploads/idlewild-archive-document-Document-c.-1950s-Idlewild-Lodge-Kitchen-Rules.jpg" width="2000" height="1525" alt=""></div>
					</div>
				</div></div></div></div></div>

</div></div></div></div></div></div><script id="script-row-unique-6" data-row="script-row-unique-6" type="text/javascript" class="vc_controls">UNCODE.initRow(document.getElementById("row-unique-6"));</script></div></div></div><div data-parent="true" class="vc_row row-container" id="row-unique-7"><div class="row limit-width row-parent"><div class="wpb_row row-inner"><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-12 single-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode_text_column text-lead" ></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">
 
<span style="font-size: 25px;"><strong>c. 1950s &#8211; Idlewild Lodge Kitchen Rules</strong></span>


<br>
A joke sign put up in Idlewild Kitchen c. 1950s. Referenced in the sign are Neil Adair, Harold Banks, Raymond Hammond, Burton Banks, Irene Hammond, Irene Adair, Geneva banks, and Jeane Banks, family friends and guests at Idlewild Lodge during that decade.

<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Transcription</strong></i></span> 



<br>
<i>"Kitchen Rules ; 1. Respect each other. The other fellow can make good coffee too – so drink his. 2. Give much thought to dirty dishes by that time some one else will have washed them. 3. Leave trash by back door. The maid has noticed that Harold never passes up a basketful. It might work for you too. 4. Discuss all grievances around the table. Each one must be satisfied. This should be interesting! 5. Committee Chairman: Broom – Neil B. Adair; Trash – Harold B. Banks; Dishes – Raymond Hammond, Understudy – Burton Banks; Rocking Chair Brigade – Irene Hammond, Geneva Banks, Irene Adair, Jeane Banks (When Available); Fish Cleaner – Burton Banks; Riot Squad – Les Dauth; Maid - Chairwoman"</i>


<br><br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>People</strong></i></span> 
<br>






Neil Adair


<br>





Harold Banks


<br>





Raymond Hammond


<br>





Burton Banks


<br>





Irene Hammond


<br>





Irene Adair


<br>





Geneva banks


<br>





Jeane Banks


<br>





Leslie Dauth


<br>





<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Details</strong></i></span> 


<br>
<i>Date: c. 1950s</i>


<br>
<i>Location: USA, Colorado, Loveland, Idlewild</i>




<br>
<i>Source: Dauth Family Archive</i>


<br>


<i>Permalink:</i>
<a href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/c-1950s-idlewild-lodge-kitchen-rules/">https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/c-1950s-idlewild-lodge-kitchen-rules/</a>



</p>
<p>
</div></div></div></div></div></div><script id="script-row-unique-7" data-row="script-row-unique-7" type="text/javascript" class="vc_controls">UNCODE.initRow(document.getElementById("row-unique-7"));</script></div></div></div>
